cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a novel approach for semantic image segmentation using multi-view RGBD data. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper mentions the use of robotic platforms for capturing indoor videos. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the proposed approach uses a convolutional neural network for segmentation. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also possible as the paper proposes an AI-based approach for semantic segmentation. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with RGBD videos and proposes a spatio-temporal pooling layer for aggregating information over space and time.
